congRepair(25.10)                                            congRepair(25.10)

Name
       congRepair - Relieves the congestion of the design

Syntax
        congRepair

       -help

       -area llx lly urx ury

       Relieves  the congestion of the design. This command performs incremen-
       tal placement based on early global route congestion  results  and  im-
       proves  the  congestion  hot  spots  by  spreading out the cells. It is
       mostly used after place_design, but sometimes it can be used after  pre
       CTS  optimization  as well. Since this command tends to move many cells
       around, it should not be run after post CTS optimization.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each congRepair .

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man congRepair

       -area <llx lly urx ury>
              Specifies the area in which congRepair will run.

              * llx: Specifies the area's lower left x coordinate.

              * lly: Specifies the area's lower left y coordinate.

              * urx: Specifies the area's upper right x coordinate.

              * ury: Specifies the area's upper right y coordinate.

              Note:  If you do not specify this option, congRepair will run on
              the complete design.

Related Information
              * place_design

